I"Â
<p>Let $n_{ij}$ be the number of pixels of class $i$ predicted to belong to class $j$, where there are $n_{cl}$ different classes, and let $t_i=\sum_jn_{ij}$ be the total number of pixels of class $i$.</p>

<ol>
  <li>pixel accuracy: $\frac{\sum\limits_i n_{ii}}{\sum\limits_i t_{i}}$</li>
  <li>mean pixel accuracy $\frac{1}{n_{cl}}\sum\limits_i \frac{n_{ii}}{ t_{i}}$</li>
  <li>mean IoU: $\frac{1}{n_{cl}}\sum\limits_i \frac{n_{ii}}{t_i+\sum\limits_j n_{ji}-n_{ii}}$</li>
  <li>frequency weighted IoU $\frac{1}{\sum\limits_k t_k}\sum\limits_i \frac{t_i n_{ii}}{t_i+\sum\limits_j n_{ji}-n_{ii}}$</li>
</ol>

<p>Reference:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Fully Convolutional Networks for Semantic Segmentation</li>
</ol>
